# Virtual Memory Optimization Tool Implementation Plan

This document outlines the technical plan for building the interactive Virtual Memory Optimization Tool.

## User Review Required
None at this stage. Please review this plan and let me know if you approve before we begin execution.

## Proposed Changes

### System Architecture
The system will be split into a Python FastAPI backend (Simulation Engine) and a Next.js React frontend (Visualization Engine).

### Backend (Python/FastAPI)
The central simulation logic holding state and executing OS simulation steps.

#### [NEW] `backend/main.py`
FastAPI application entry point. Will define REST endpoints (`/api/simulate`) and WebSocket endpoints for real-time visualization streaming.

#### [NEW] `backend/models.py`
Pydantic models for API requests (e.g. Memory Size, Page Size, Reference String) and responses.

#### [NEW] `backend/simulation/memory_manager.py`
Contains `PagingManager`, `PageTable`, and `FrameTable` to handle address translation and memory state mapping.

#### [NEW] `backend/simulation/algorithms.py`
Implementation of `FIFO`, `LRU`, and `Optimal` page replacement algorithms.

#### [NEW] `backend/simulation/page_fault_handler.py`
Logic to trigger page replacements and track statistics.

### Frontend (Next.js/React)
A rich, dark-mode, animated dashboard for input and visualization.

#### [NEW] `frontend/package.json`
Next.js app configuration with Framer Motion, Tailwind CSS, and Recharts.

#### [NEW] `frontend/app/page.tsx`
Main dashboard layout combining the input sidebar and the simulation canvas.

#### [NEW] `frontend/components/InputPanel.tsx`
Form to configure memory size, page size, frames, reference string, and choose algorithms.

#### [NEW] `frontend/components/MemoryGrid.tsx`
Visual representation of RAM (frames) and Disk (pages).

#### [NEW] `frontend/components/SimulationControls.tsx`
Play/Pause/Step controls communicating context state to the dashboard.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Create Python unit tests for the core page replacement algorithms (`test_algorithms.py`).
- Validate standard inputs (e.g. 7 0 1 2 0 3 0 4) against expected fault counts (FIFO=6).

### Manual Verification
- Start the FastAPI server and Next.js dev server.
- Visually confirm animations trigger smoothly on page faults.
- Verify that performance graphs accurately reflect backend statistics.
